The paper focuses on graph-to-sequence transduction models for natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of graph neural networks and transformer models also suggests that it may be relevant to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on text generation and translation, which suggests that it may also be relevant to Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) for tasks such as image captioning.
